.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE WIELKANOC-5 M "25 Mar 88" 1989
.RZ "PIECZEN BARANIHA Z PIECA" "Roast Leg of Lamb"
.IH "Serves 8\-12"
.IG "" "vinegar"
.IG "1" "leg of lamb"
.IG "6" "cloves garlic,"
cut into slivers
.IG "" "salt and pepper"
.SK 1
Soak a towel with vinegar; wrap around the leg of lamb and let stand overnight.
.SK 2
Remove towel. Trim off fell and excess fat.  Make small slits in the fat cover
on meat.  Push a sliver of garlic into each slit.
.SK 3
Place lamb, fat side up, on rack in a roasting pan.  Sprinkle with salt and
pepper.
.SK 4
Roast at
.TE 325 160
until done as desired.  Allow 30 minutes per pound
for medium and 35 minutes per pound for well-done.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
2\-3 hours.
.I Precision:
No need to measure.
.WR
Original recipe passed down through the generations and translated from
Polish into English by
Edward Chrzanowski
MFCF, University of Waterloo, Waterloo, Ontario, Canada
echrzanowski@watmath.waterloo.edu  or {decvax,att,utzoo}!watmath!echrzanowski
